description: Gets the contents of a network package. A network package is a .zip file in CSAR (Cloud Service Archive) format defines the function packages you want to deploy and the Amazon Web Services infrastructure you want to deploy them on.

parameters.name: accept
parameters.description: The format of the package you want to download from the network package.

parameters.name: nsdInfoId
parameters.description: ID of the network service descriptor in the network package.

nested_items.name: contentType
nested_items.description: Indicates the media type of the resource.

nested_items.name: nsdContent
nested_items.description: Content of the network service descriptor in the network package.
